03/06/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan announced a cabinet reshuffle on Thursday (2 June), following the resignations of three ministers. He told reporters that Agriculture Minister Sami Guclu, Civil Works and Housing Minister Zeki Ergezen and Womens' Affairs State Minister Guldal Aksit had submitted their resignations. There had been reports in the local media that the three were about to be sacked due to poor performance. 
In other news, Turkish Cypriot leader Memmet Ali Talat arrived in Ankara on Thursday with Prime Minister Ferdi Sabit Soyer and Foreign Minister Serdar Denktash. The three are meeting with Erdogan and Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul. (AFP, TurkishPress.com - 02/06/05)
